Fifty-seven patients were followed for 2 years and 34 patients for 3 years in a 
study of the CeraOne system. One implant was lost, resulting in a cumulative 
success rate of 97.3% at the 3-year examination. All-ceramic crowns were seated 
for 95% of the subjects, and only four of the crowns were classified as 
failures. Two all-ceramic crowns fractured following trauma, but no crown was 
